==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Improbable
<hw>Im*prob"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>improbabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>probabilis</ets> probable: cf. F. <ets>improbable</ets>. See
<er>Probable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not probable; unlikely to be true; not to
be expected under the circumstances or in the usual course of events;
<as>as, an <ex>improbable</ex> story or event</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He . . . sent to Elutherius, then bishop of Rome, an
<qex>improbable</qex> letter, as some of the contents discover.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im*prob"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Im*prob"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improbate</ent>⟦br⟧
